\f1\b\fs48 \cf0 Prompt/instru\'e7\'e3o para aplicar no design\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Use isto como dire\'e7\'e3o para o Figma Make/Codex/design:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 Redesign the game HUD using a \'93marine biologist field journal\'94 aesthetic.\
\
The interface should look like a field diary used to observe and care for a rare baby mermaid creature. Avoid futuristic, metallic, glossy, neon, RPG-like or generic mobile game UI. Replace dark gradient panels, heavy glows and shiny buttons with paper-like cards, observation labels, hand-drawn icons, subtle ink lines, field notes, stamps, tags and soft aquatic colors.\
\
The top HUD should become an observation sheet/card with a light paper texture, subtle blue ink borders, small field-journal details like clips, tabs, stamps or handwritten-style labels. It should display the creature stage, age, current layer, sparkle count and biological status meters.\
\
Status bars should feel like biological observation meters, not RPG health bars. Use named indicators such as hunger, energy, mood and bond/curiosity. The meters should have a soft hand-drawn or watercolor-like style with small scale marks.\
\
The event message should become a small field note or observation card, not a dark pill button. Replace emoji with a custom wave icon in the same hand-drawn style.\
\
The bottom action buttons should become journal action cards or page tabs. Remove heavy glow, dark gradients and excessive shadows. Use neutral paper-like surfaces with subtle colored accents only on icons, borders, stamps or small markers. Keep the actions readable but make them feel like part of a research notebook.\
\
Create a consistent custom icon set with thin hand-drawn aquatic line icons: compass for explore, algae for feed, moon/bubbles for rest, starfish or badge for challenge, checklist for objective, shell/coral shelter for refuge, arrows with bubbles for layer navigation, folded map/current for travel.\
\
Use a restrained palette: off-white paper, pale sand, soft aqua, deep blue ink, muted teal, coral accents, algae green and warm yellow for rewards. Avoid using a different strong glow color for every button.\
\
All UI elements should feel like they belong to the same field journal system: cards, notes, labels, stamps, tabs, checklists and observation sheets. Keep the layout clean, readable and minimal, but give it personality through the diary metaphor.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa321\partightenfactor0

